| FTC Threatens Spyware Distributors With Prison                     |
|   from the truth-to-the-situation dept.                            |
|   posted by Zonk on Wednesday April 11, @03:36 (Security)          |
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/11/0724215           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Federal regulator Mark Pryor, in a Senate Commerce Committee hearing, has
stated that [0]spyware distributors should face harsher penalties than
fees. His solution: imprisonment. "Federal Trade Commissioner William
Kovacic said most wrongdoers in the spyware arena 'can only be described
as vicious organized criminals. Many of most serious wrongdoers we
observed in this area, I believe, are only going to be deterred if their
freedom is withdrawn,' so it's important for the FTC to collaborate on
its cases with criminal law enforcement authorities, Kovacic said."

Discuss this story at:
    http://it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/11/0724215

