| OLED TVs Arriving Within the Next Three Years                      |
|   from the cooler-screens-but-not-shows dept.                      |
|   posted by CowboyNeal on Wednesday April 11, @13:08 (Displays)    |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/11/1624257     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Anonymous Howard writes "Toshiba and Matsushita, in a joint venture, are
going to be [0]bringing OLED TV panels to market within 3 years! Granted,
the size of the panel is only 20.8 inches, but that is a huge step up
from the small OLED screens used in cell phones and other portable
devices. It will have a resolution of 1,280 by 768 pixels (WXGA) and
handles 16.7 million colors. No specifications on contrast, brightness,
or refresh rates have been released, but such specs wouldn't necessarily
be indicative of OLED displays to be released in three years' time."

